Sentencas: Coking on the conventional Ni-based anode is a grand challenge for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: In this work, a new type of coking-tolerant composite anode material, with a composition of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta, has been identified and evaluated on Y0.08Zr0.92O1.96 electrolyte-supported cells.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction analysis indicates that the crystal structure of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta is relatively stable in wet air, while active nanoparticles of FeNi3 are in situ exsolved from the parent perovskite oxides in pure hydrogen.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: A peak power density of 439 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C is achieved from the cell with Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta anode when fueled by hydrogen.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: More importantly, addition of Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta in the anode can further improve the performance and stability.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: The cell with Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta composite anode achieves a maximum power density of 551, 476 and 392 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C when the anode is fueled by hydrogen, syngas and methane, respectively.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ

Sentencas: The cell has shown negligible degradation for 210 hs in syngas and 600 hs in methane fuel, indicating that the Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta is a promising anode for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A Promising Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-δ
